    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it doesn't feel temporary though. it feels permanent. like the \"me\" that could paint, the person who had a reason to wake up, is just gone. i'm just a body moving through a room. it's like the vessel is still here but the contents are empty. what's the point of even maintaining the shell if there's nothing left inside to fill it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
